original: Danielsson, Bertil Svensk Ariel, kyrkoherde, Alvesta, f. 4/10/91 i Kär-da, Jönköp. 1., av kontr :prost Nils D. o. Maria Dahlqvist. G. 22 m. Maria Ingrid Antoinette Möllerberg. Barn: Kerstin f. 23, Nils-Bertil 25, Gunnar 27, Bengt 28, Barbro 30, Märtha o. Birgitta 33. — Stud:ex. 10, teol. kand. 15. Kommin. i Vissefjärda 19, kyrkoh. i Hemmesjö 25, dito i Aringsås sed. 33, fäng:pastor, timlär. v. Alvesta komm. mellansk.
translated: Danielsson, Bertil Svensk Ariel, clergyman (also referred to as "kyrkoherde" in Swedish), of Alvesta. Born on October 4th, 1891, in Kär-da, Jönköping county, the first child of district dean Nils D. and Maria Dahlqvist. Married to Maria Ingrid Antoinette Möllerberg in 1922. They had six children: Kerstin born in 1923, Nils-Bertil in 1925, Gunnar in 1927, Bengt in 1928, Barbro in 1930, and twins Märtha and Birgitta born in 1933. Bertil passed his studentexamen (equivalent to high school diploma) in 1910 and completed his Bachelor of Theology degree in 1915. He served as a curate in Vissefjärda from 1919, then as a vicar (also known as "kyrkoh") in Hemmesjö from 1925 to 1933, followed by the same position in Aringsås. He also worked as a prison chaplain and a part-time teacher in the Alvesta municipality.
